<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-187-168  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 187 168.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Feb 12 1990 v19 n10p30(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Monotype's &quot;Classic Fonts&quot; ready.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Monotype Typography Inc. (product introduction).andO;Topic:     FontsSoftware PackagesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Monotype has announced that its entire library of more than 300 Type 3PostScript fonts is available in its new Classic Fonts series starting onFeb. 1, 1990.andP;  Classic Fonts, based on the original Monotype designs, employa grid-fitting routine for improving quality at low resolutions.andP;  Featuresinclude compatibility with ATM, data compression of up to 60% compared toType 3 format and compatibility with Type 3 and Type 1 formats.andP;  Monotypesaid it will phase out its Type 3 font library but that it still will developits Type 1 hinted fonts, in addition to the Classic Fonts that use gridfitting rather than the hinting and regularizing algorithm of its Type 1library.andP;  Four to six new packages of Classic Fonts and two to three packagesof Type 1 fonts are scheduled for release monthly this year.andO;</TEXT></DOC>